HEADWORD: Xanthomelanous
<hw>Xan`tho*mel"a*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>xantho-</ets> + Gr. <?/, <?/, black.]</ety> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the lighter division of the Melanochroi, or
those races having an olive or yellow complexion and black
hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

